I’ve put a full, ready-to-run Python script in the canvas called “Cisco Compliance Checker.” It:

connects to a Cisco device with Netmiko

pulls show running-config

uses ciscoconfparse (a separate library) to perform compliance checks for logging, AAA, banner, and ACLs

outputs a CSV or HTML report (your choice)

How to use
Install deps:

bash
Copy
Edit
pip install netmiko ciscoconfparse pyyaml
(Optional) Create a policy file policy.yaml to customize rules (a sample is embedded at the top of the script).

Run it:

bash
Copy
Edit
# HTML report
python cisco_compliance_checker.py \
  --host 192.0.2.10 --username admin --password 'p@ss' \
  --device-type cisco_ios --output html --outfile results.html --policy policy.yaml

# CSV report
python cisco_compliance_checker.py \
  --host 192.0.2.10 --username admin --password 'p@ss' \
  --device-type cisco_ios --output csv --outfile results.csv
It returns PASS/FAIL/WARN/INFO for each check and exits non-zero if any FAIL occurs (handy for CI).

Want me to tweak the policy defaults or add more checks (NTP, SNMP, interfaces, crypto, etc.)?

======================
I’ve added NTP and SNMP compliance checks into the script:

NTP: Verifies NTP servers are configured and optionally enforces ntp authenticate.

SNMP: Flags default public/private community strings and optionally enforces SNMPv3 users.

Do you want me to also update the sample policy YAML at the top so you can customize NTP/SNMP requirements, similar to the logging/AAA rules?
